                claw:debug "Failed to fetch recent message for $im:$chatid"
                latest_msg="[unavailable]"
            } ;;
    esac
    claw:info --m:latest_msg "$latest_msg" "Processing agent request for $im:$chatid"
    case "$im" in
        weixin)
            ___x_cmd agent request  \
                --timeout 1800 \
                --debug \
                --workspace "$workspace_dir"  \
                --reference-workspace "$___X_CMD_CLAW_AGENT_REFERENCE_WS" \
                "You have received a message from a user via WeChat.
${first_contact_prompt}

REPLY METHOD:
Use the command 'x weixin send' to reply:
- For help:        x weixin send -h
- For text:        x weixin send --text '<msg>'
  IMPORTANT: Do NOT use \\n for line breaks. The text \\n will be printed literally (two characters: backslash + n).
  CORRECT — press Enter for actual line breaks inside the quotes:
    '<msg>' becomes 'Line 1
    Line 2
    Line 3'
  WRONG — \\n appears as literal text in the output:
    'Line 1\\nLine 2\\nLine 3'
- For image/video: x weixin send --image <path>  or  x weixin send --video <path>

FORMAT:
WeChat has limited formatting support — no tables, no headings, partial markdown. Prefer plain text, bullet lists, and emoji.

CRON EXAMPLES:
  In claw context, ONLY \`x claw cron\` is allowed. Do NOT use:
  - CronCreate/CronDelete (Claude Code built-in, only works in active session)
  - Any system scheduling tools (cron, at, etc.)
  - \`x claw cron\` is the ONLY choice — it persists after agent exit.
- x claw cron --help
- x claw cron add --name \"<name>\" --desc \"<desc>\" \"<cron_expr>\" \"x claw agentrequest $im $chatid '<msg>'\"
  Requirements: <msg> is sent to a NEW agent with NO memory. It MUST include Goal, Tools, Steps, Output, and how to deliver results. Use SINGLE quotes.
  BAD:  'Check HN' (too vague, the agent won't know what to do).
  GOOD: 'Use x hn top for top 5 posts. Extract title, URL, score. Send: x weixin send --text '<formatted_list>''

Your workspace: \"$workspace_dir\"

Current time: '$(___x_cmd date iso)'
